** Intermediate or Senior Structural Engineer, New Plymouth, Taranaki **   
** $90,000 - $150,000 + $5k sign on bonus and relocation **   
** All experience levels considered. **   
** **   
** $90k-$150k + $5k sign on bonus and relocation + Flexible working + Variety of projects + Active social + Personal training budget + Health insurance + Phone + Company wellness program **   
**   
The Company **  
** **   
This is a fantastic opportunity for a talented Structural Engineer to join a
leading mid-sized multi-disciplinary consultancy in the busy New Plymouth
region. My client is a very well established business with a great local
reputation and a very strong portfolio of future projects. All experience
levels will be considered for this role.  
  
They provide expertise across a very wide range of work covering structural,
civil and geotechnical projects for the residential, commercial, industrial
and oil and gas sectors.  
  
They pride themselves on not only having a high technical level but also a
great culture, with an enthusiastic team who take a fresh approach to provide
solutions to their clients. The team takes a collaborative approach across all
project areas.  
  
If joining at experienced Graduate to Intermediate level then this is a great
opportunity to join a consultancy where you will work collaboratively across
different project streams across a wide variety of projects in a mid-sized
business where you will play a big part in their success so this is a great
chance to increase your engineering skills-set, project exposure and profile
to really grow your career.  
  
If joining at Senior level then you will have an opportunity to take a high-
level, lead role in the business and really stamp your mark on the built
environment in Taranaki as well as having possible scope towards future
Directorship.  
  
Alongside excellent career growth the business is also human centred, they
place a very high importance on work life balance by facilitating healthy
lifestyles, keeping an active social calendar and allowing flexible working
hours.  
  
** The Role **   
** **   
The successful applicant will be involved in the opportunity to provide
technical input as you work alongside their diverse team on some of the
country’s most interesting buildings and Structural Engineering projects.  
  
The role will include a balance of office based design, site visits and
construction monitoring across a wide range of work.  
  

  * Structural engineering design for residential, commercial and a minor portion of industrial projects. 
  * Residential design includes SED elements of new residential buildings, retaining walls and foundation designs. 
  * Commercial projects include earthquake assessments and strengthening and new commercial buildings. 
  * Senior engineers would be expected to work with and review the work of junior engineers. 
** About You **   
** **   

  * We would consider all levels, but lean more towards an intermediate or senior engineer but an experienced Graduate of 2-3 years would be considered also. 
  * CPEng is not compulsory, however a long-term goal to gain CPEng would be expected 
  * A Bachelor of Engineering (Civil) or equivalent qualification 
  * Structural engineering design for residential, commercial and a minor portion of industrial projects. 
  * Commercial projects include earthquake assessments and strengthening and new commercial buildings. 
  * Experience with pedestrian, road and farm bridges would also be preferred. 
  * Residential design includes SED elements of new residential buildings, retaining walls and foundation designs. 
  * Senior engineers would be expected to work with and review the work of junior engineers. 
  * Have strong interpersonal and technical skills 
  * Creative thinking to find innovative solutions for our clients 
  * Experience in Microsoft Office programs 
  * Experience with typical structural analysis software is preferred 
  * Be enthusiastic and willing work on a wide range of structural engineering projects 
  
** The Benefits **   
** **   

  * Salary range for intermediate would be $90k to $110k. Seniors $120k to $150k (CPEng). 
  * $5k sign on bonus and relocation 
  * High importance on work life balance by facilitating healthy lifestyles, keeping an active social calendar and allowing flexible working hours. 
  * They will help develop your engineering career by offering a unique training program and set training budget for each staff member that must be used each year. 
  * Health insurance, cell phone 
  * Flexible working hours 
  * On-going training and career progression opportunities 
  * A wellness Program linking employee and organisational health 
  
  
